reviewText: First and foremost, the graphics are beautiful! I think that's part of the reason my daughter loves the DVD so much. Secondly, the songs are very catchy. At first, I admit that I didn't like some of the songs, but they grew on me. My daughter loves all of them. I think that "Twinkle Twinkle Little Star" would have been awesome with a fast beat, but it's cute as a lullaby.

reviewText: I bought this for a birthday present for my 1-year-old nephew. He has been watching parts of it on YouTube so I thought this would be a great gift that would give his parents a break. It calms him right down. Good length for short attention spans. Great, catchy tunes. Even my 5-year-old sings along with it. Adults may find themselves humming the tunes too.

reviewText: Seriously this is the best DVD I have ever purchased from my kids! My four year old was completely entranced by the songs/videos. He danced and sang along. Even my twelve year old didn’t want to leave the room; while he didn’t dance and sing he was entranced by the video. I should note that both children have autism and this DVD really brought a smile to both of their faces. I can’t wait to buy volume 2.
summary: Bring a child out of their shell

reviewText: This is the best video for babies/toddlers that I have ever seen. We have 3 in our home, a set of 3 month-old twins and a 21 month-old toddler. All 3 love the video. The toddler dances with the music of the snappier tunes and tries to sing along. She loves the "Twinkle, Twinkle Little Star" song at the end, especially where the star kisses the Kooky bird. This is the last song and is an excellent ending because it is quiet and peaceful.The twins watch the screen raptly. The boy coos and chatters along with the music, while the girl never takes her eyes off of the screen.This was the best $15 I have ever spent. I am waiting impatiently for the second DVD to come out.

reviewText: I ran into gigglebellies while searching on my smart phone for a Twinkle Twinkle video to soothe my (then 9 week old) baby. I eventually bought Vol.1 so she could watch/hear all the songs in full versions...and after a few days, she let me know just how much she appreciated it. At 3 months and 1 day, her first full sentence was "I love you!" ..repeated 6 or 7 times loudly while we played Peanut for her. She really seems to like Peanut and Kooky Bird. Up til then...she would coo/gurgle "loveyou", not always distinctly--so it seems she was motivated by her joy with Peanut to tell us the phrase that she's heard us say to her so often.  Thanks, GIgglebellies -- we'll be getting more of this product!
